args: You trained pretty hard today, Lowen.\nMake sure to wipe off all your sweat\nso you don't catch cold.
Now that you mention it, I might be a little\nhungry—but I think I'd like to try and make\nsomething myself.
No, don't trouble yourself. Stay here and\nI'll whip something up.
(It's happening slowly, but everyone is\nstarting to rely on me more—except for\nCleo, that is.)
(At this rate, I'll never get her to stop\ntreating me like a baby brother.)
(I have to get her to recognize that I've\ngrown, but how do I DO that?)
Cleo! Cleeeo!\nDid you already start making the food?
I was just about to get started.\nIs something the matter?
No! I just need you to let me take care\nof it.
Take a load off, Cleo! Rest those dogs!\nI've got lunch handled today.
Come oooon! You gotta trust me with this\nstuff sometime!
All right! Lemme start by whipping up\nsome soup. I think I remember Louise's\nrecipe pretty well...
So I cut the potatoes liiiike...this, right?
Curl your fingers! CURL YOUR FINGERS!\nYou'll lop them off otherwise!
Right! Curled fingers, okay. Now then,\neverything is diced up, so we throw the\nveggies into the boiling water.
Oh man, that water's hot! And there's\nsteam everywhere. Maybe I'll just stand\nway back here and toss the veggies into—
You will most certainly NOT do that!\nThe boiling water could splash out and\nscald the flesh right off your bones!
I, uh, don't know if it's THAT hot, but\nsure. Lemme just drop them in real\ngently... Yeowch! Hot!
Be careful, for the love of the goddess!
(He's going to kill himself right in my own\nkitchen. Someone save me...)
You finished, but... Urgh... I feel dizzy...
Are you okay, Cleo? You look completely\nexhausted!
I think...I may have worried about you\novermuch...
I'm sorry. This is all my fault.
I just wanted to help you out, Cleo.\nThen you could see how much I've grown\nand maybe you'd—
I know, Lowen. It's all right.
But I made you totally exhausted because\nI was so wrapped up in myself.
Accepting the ways in which we might be\nwanting is all part of maturing.
Heh. I guess I'm still pretty uncool, huh?
I thought I had everything figured out,\nbut I just ended up making trouble for you.
Even grown-ups have their flaws, Lowen.

We make unsound decisions, panic,
and let our emotions get the best of us.
We're often more like children than
children in that respect.
But the difference is that we recognize\nour mistakes and fight through them.
Becoming an adult doesn't mean that\nyour problems all suddenly disappear.
Still, I imagine none of this will dissuade\nyou from attempting to grow up as fast\nas you possibly can.
I wanna become a strong adult who can\nprotect the people that are important\nto him.
Heh. But you're plenty strong\nenough already, Lowen.
Er, but weren't you just super worried\nabout how I'd kill myself while making\na pot of soup?
You're able to pursue your aspirations with\ngenuine fervor.
And that comes from your own strength.\nNothing else.
So I have strength even though I'm still\ngrowing up? Hmm...
Hey, Cleo? Do you think it's possible to\nbe an adult AND a little brother?
The only person who can answer that\nquestion is you, Lowen.
But before we continue this conversation,\nlet's try your soup. I'm simply famished.

Oh, and now that you've proven yourself in
my kitchen, I'll be assigning you meal
prep duties. I assume you're all right
with this arrangement?
Of course! Er, but there might still be\nSOME things I can't do.
But I know you'll teach me how to do 'em\nwhen the time comes, right, Cleo?!
